Case Study 1: Improving Delivery Predictability by 30%
Context:
Teams struggled with inconsistent sprint delivery, rollover, and unclear acceptance criteria.
Actions:
Introduced structured backlog refinement with story slicing.
Coached PO on clarity of commitments and acceptance criteria.
Implemented velocity trend analysis and realistic forecasting.
Strengthened Daily Scrum discipline to surface blockers early.
 Outcome:
 Delivery predictability improved by 30%
 Sprint rollover reduced significantly
 Stakeholders gained better visibility and trust
Case Study 2: Removing Technical Blockers and Stabilizing iOS Builds
Context:
Mobile developers faced slow, unstable iOS build environments.
Actions:
Collaborated with engineering to build a reliable AWS EC2 mac2.metal environment.
Automated daily environment resets to avoid configuration drift.
Documented workflows and shared best practices with the team.
Used my technical knowledge to translate issues clearly between Product and DevOps.
 Outcome:
 Faster and more stable builds
 Reduced engineering frustration
Case Study 3: Establishing Agile Standards for Distributed Teams
Context:
Teams lacked unified ways of working, causing confusion and delivery delays.
Actions:
Developed internal Agile playbooks, templates, and working agreements.
Standardized sprint workflow from refinement → planning → execution → review.
Set up unified Jira dashboards for progress tracking.
Outcome:
Teams worked with consistent expectations
Improved transparency across Product & Engineering
Reduced friction during ceremonies and hand-offs

